abstract: >-
  Regula is an open-source command-line tool that combines code scanning
  with governance questionnaires for EU AI Act compliance at the point
  of creation. It detects
  Article 5 prohibited practices, Annex III high-risk categories, and
  Annex I cross-references; maps every finding to specific articles of
  Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 and 12 compliance frameworks (ISO 42001,
  NIST AI RMF, NIST CSF, SOC 2, ISO 27001, OWASP LLM Top 10,
  MITRE ATLAS, EU CRA, LGPD, Marco Legal IA, UK ICO);
  generates Annex IV conformity evidence packs and Annex VIII
  registration packets; and maintains a SHA-256 hash-chained tamper-
  evident audit log. It runs entirely on the user's local machine with
  zero runtime dependencies. Precision and recall are published with
  reproducible methodology; see docs/benchmarks/PRECISION_RECALL_2026_04.md.
